# ## Finding the metascore location

# ![nr_votes.png](attachment:nr_votes.png)

# The name attribute is different from the class attribute. Using BeautifulSoup we can access elements by any attribute. The find() and find_all() functions have a parameter named attrs. To this we can pass in the attributes and values we are searching for as a dictionary:
# 

# ![20_span.png](attachment:20_span.png)

# In[58]:


# type the above code to isolate the votes

first_votes = first_movie.find('span', attrs = {'name' : 'nv'})
first_votes


# You can treat a Tag object just like a dictionary. The HTML attributes are the dictionary’s keys. The values of the HTML attributes are the values of the dictionary’s keys. This is how we can access the value of the data-value attribute:
# 

# ## Putting the lists together

# Now that you have found all of the tags to isolate the individual elements, you can put it all together and collect all of the films on the page.

# ![21_lists.png](attachment:21_lists.png)

# In[59]:


#Type in the above code to create a list

names = []
years = []
imdb_ratings = []
metascores = []
votes = []


# ![containerloop.png](attachment:containerloop.png)

# In[61]:


#type the above code in collect all of the film information.

for container in movie_containers:
    if container.find('div', class_ = 'ratings-metascore') is not None:
        name = container.h3.a.text
        names.append(name)
        year = container.h3.find('span', class_ = 'lister-item-year').text
        years.append(year)
        imdb = float(container.strong.text)
        imdb_ratings.append(imdb)
        m_score = container.find('span', class_ = 'metascore').text
        metascores.append(int(m_score))
        vote = container.find('span', attrs = {'name' : 'nv'})['data-value']
        votes.append(int(vote))


# ![pandas.png](attachment:pandas.png)

# In[64]:


#run the code in the above cell to turn into a pandas dataframe and find the information about it.

import pandas as pd

test_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'movie' : names,
    'year' : years,
    'imdb' : imdb_ratings,
    'metascore' : metascores,
    'votes' : votes
})

print(test_df.info())
test_df

